	<p>Watch the following video to learn more about capacitors.</p>
		
    <video youtube="8lcFW_AyXmg"><description>An introduction to capacitors.</description></video>
	
	<p>A capacitor is made up of two conductors separated by an insulator.</p>
	
	<definition xml:id="capacitance">
		<title>Capacitance</title>
		<statement>
			<p>The <term>Capacitance</term> of a capacitor is defined as <me>C = Q / \Delta V</me> and is often dependent on the geometry of the capacitor. The units of capacitance are in farads (F). </p>
		</statement>
	</definition>


